tweets.content:
Franklin Templeton's tokenized Money Market Fund BENJI earned ~$121k in management fees in August but paid only $28 in gas (0.02%).

The direct revenue from most RWAs can be minimal. To understand their real value to a blockchain ecosystem, we can classify them:

Platinum Tier â€“ High Velocity
â€¢ Assets integrated with high-transaction activities like payments or trading
â€¢ Example: Stablecoins or tokenized stocks

Gold Tier â€“ Highly Composable
â€¢ RWAs powering high-velocity activities like stablecoins, credit, derivatives, or settlement, adding transparency vs off-chain collateral
â€¢ Brings network effects: trust, branding, institutional adoption
â€¢ Example: Securitizeâ€™s BUIDL as USDtb collateral

Silver Tier â€“ Distributed & Primary Market Focused
â€¢ Onboards large user bases onchain but limited composability
â€¢ Example: Spikoâ€™s USTBL/EUTBL

Bronze Tier â€“ Low Activity
â€¢ Few holders, zero on-chain transactions, low primary market volume
â€¢ Only for inflating RWA metrics for social media

Not all RWAs are created equal. On-chain velocity, composability, and utility matter far more than headline AUM.
